# v1.0.0.1 - 09-29-2025
- fix arg_count for dynamic format strings

# v1.0.0.0 - 09-27-2025
- Major performance optimization: avoid dynamic allocations in logging path
  - Refactor logging engine to use pre-allocated argument storage
  - Add separate string queue for efficient dynamic string handling
  - Introduce typed argument system with improved format string detection
  - Add SLICK_LOGGER_MAX_ARGS define (default: 20) for argument limit
- Fix Linux build issues
- Update benchmark

# v0.2.0.0 - 09-23-2025
- Add dedicated sink functionality: sinks with dedicated flag set to true only receive messages logged directly to them, not broadcast messages from LOG_* macros
- Improve sink-level log filtering documentation and examples
- Update slick_queue to v1.0.1.2

# v0.1.1.1 - 09-16-2025
- Fixed x86 build warning

# v0.1.1.0 - 09-12-2025
- Change organization name

# v0.1.0.3 - 09-08-2025
- Add file_path() getter to FileSink for path retrieval
- Add get_sink<SinkT> to Logger for retrieving sinks by type
- Update CMakeLists.txt to auto-generate header with warning messages from src/logger.hpp
- Modified DailyFileSink to also support size-based rotation.

# v0.1.0.2 - 09-03-2025
- Replace raw pointers with std::unique_ptr for SlickQueue to ensure automatic memory cleanup  
- Add shutdown() calls in init() functions to safely stop the logger before re-initialization  
- Introduce validation checks to enforce proper sink configuration  

# v0.1.0.1 - 8-30-2025
- Update to SlickQueue v1.0.0.2
- Add CHANGELOG
- Fix examples build
- Log version on start
- Add installation rules for include directory and custom targets for automated distribution and packaging in Release mode.
